{
  "texts": [
    "Reward-Weighted LearningRLHF and reward-based fine-tuning.",
    "Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) [4] has become a widely used paradigm for aligning large models with human preferences.",
    "By combining supervised fine-tuning with reward models and reinforcement learning (e.g., PPO), LLMs can be guided to generate outputs that align with human values.",
    "These methods demonstrate that reward-weighted objectives can substantially improve the quality and coherence of generated content.Motivation for reward integration in PEFT.",
    "The concept of rewardweighted learning, while originally developed for RLHF and alignment, has strong potential for improving supervised PEFT methods."
  ]
}